      "timestamp_label": "491:52:00",
      "transcript_text": "A generational opportunity for programming for older adults and children and support the healthcare needs of our city. The partnership with the county has been long standing and as a result, the city is able to do more for the residents than they would otherwise be able to do. For instance, on social services, emergency dispatch, libraries, court services, and schools, to name a few. Without these partnerships, the cost to our residents would be significantly more if we had to provide these basic services on our own. I've been a lifelong proponent of continuous improvement in organizations, and while the Willard Sherwood center is not an organization, it is a joint partnership with the county that needs to be continuously improved and nurtured to avoid even further costs. As an older adult, which I'm getting older and older by the minute, I support the Willard Sherwood center project because participating in programs at Green Acres is potentially hazardous to my physical well being. When I attended events at the Green Acres Center, I had had recent knee surgery and since parking at the Green Acres center is at a premium, walking to the entrance was very difficult and walking down those steps to get to the front door was even more difficult. And then once you get inside the building, you have more steps to get to some of the rooms and that gets increasingly difficult for the older people. Get having access to new modernized Willard Sterwood Center.",
