      "transcript_text": "Good evening. I'm John Cho. I live at 3421 Preservation Drive, the community of Pickett's Reserve. And on behalf of Dick Cardinale, the president of our HOA, and the 88 HOA members, I I am delivering a simple message, and that is a thank you. Thank you for your leadership, and thank you for prioritizing safety. About a month ago, we had two council members, not in my community, but in the community right across the street at Sutton Heights, and we also received some information from Barrister's Keep, who's across the street, very interested in ensuring that Pickett's Road is safe for children, for anyone walking. We understand that soon-to-be softball park will be down below and that there are some changes afoot with the refinery. But we know that through Yuliana's vote that you decided, and 3 is a charm, to proceed with reaching out to the county and hopefully we'll get the $80,000 for this regional study. I do ask, and we've discussed this as a community, to consider something. As a cardiac surgeon, we often say, and I learned at Mayo Clinic, to measure twice, cut once, and that if you're able to get the money in fiscal year '27, that it be done early in the year if the study is completed, and that you do consider a moratorium on any development or any changes in that refinery until that study is completed and the changes required are taken care of before any development or further development or transition at that refinery occurs. Thanks for your consideration. Thanks again for your leadership. Great job.",
