      "timestamp_label": "2096:55:49",
      "transcript_text": "So Councilmember Peterson, correct, it does not affect our potential rating, yet issuing a referendum or not issuing a referendum, there is a defined time frame when a referendum is approved when debt has to be issued against that. 8 years is typically what the range is with the potential 2-year extension that you would need to get the circuit court involved and ask them for another 2 years beyond that. Once that— that's the window that's established. So similarly, because we are kind of talking about Wheeler Sherwood, I think in a previous presentation that we are at year 12 right now. So if we would have potentially issued a referendum at the beginning or at the beginning stages ages of that, we would be butting up against that 8-10 year mark right now. So just for consideration.",
      "snippet": "So Councilmember Peterson, correct, it does not affect our potential rating, yet issuing a referendum or not issuing a referendum, there is a defined time frame when a referendum is approved when debt has to be issued a…"
