      "transcript_text": "[Speaker:COMMISSIONER MAY] Well, and part of my reason for asking is it's, I think, not uncommon for major capital projects to work off of 25-year lifespans, things like that. And to go ahead and model out and forecast out what the performance will be over the lifetime of the project, recognizing you get less certain as you go forward. But at the same time, often the investments were predicated on a project lifespan and an OPEX and CAPEX stream associated with that at the outset. And so I think that's really what's being asked here is what would that look like. And where would that leave us in terms of obligations that we have, you know, going past this next decade? I think it would be useful, I think, as a policy matter and a planning matter, I think, for these kinds of projects, whatever these life— project lifespans are, it would be good to plan across that whole horizon so we could see what that looks like.",
