      "timestamp_label": "4052:48:17",
      "transcript_text": "You said something that made me think about something else. Um, I know, um, Mr. Alexander, when we spoke before, I asked about the budget memos and I asked about the resident questions that come. And if I remember correctly, you said that when residents email, those don't become budget memos. It's only when council asks questions. And I'm wondering if given the extraordinary amount of time that you all have spent responding to some very specific questions that others may have, is there a way that we could, you know, remove a person's name and anything else that might be identifying and post those questions in whatever format they're already in without doing any other work to put them in alphabetical order or this or that or even categorizing them? Just here's the information, because you have gone to such great depths to answer the questions. I've learned from the questions as well, but it also seems like what we're finding is that a lot of people have similar questions, right? And so I think that if we can do that— if not, then I'll generate a new budget memo and ask new questions, and you can copy and paste.",
