      "start_seconds": 442,
      "timestamp_label": "07:22",
      "transcript_text": "Now we're going to take a look a little bit of those students that I was talking about earlier, about who they are and how many are in our schools currently. The information that you see on the screen is enrollment information or membership information from September 30th of 2025, so the start of this school year. And what you're seeing is two sets of information. One on the left is our city students and on the right is Fairfax County Public Schools overall. And it's a comparison between the first day of school this year and the first day of school last year. And so you can see a lot of blue down arrows. And what we saw regionally in Northern Virginia is a downward trend in enrollment. So students that ended last year on the last day of school, a smaller amount of students showed up on the first day of school. And this is not anything that was unique to the city of Fairfax or Fairfax County Public School. There were measurable decreases in Loudoun, Arlington, Prince William, Montgomery County, Maryland, and several of our surrounding districts.",
      "snippet": "Now we're going to take a look a little bit of those students that I was talking about earlier, about who they are and how many are in our schools currently. The information that you see on the screen is enrollment info…"
