      "turn_index": 4,
      "start_seconds": 262504,
      "timestamp_label": "72:55:04",
      "transcript_text": "Perfect microphone height. Um, yeah, so this week is Invasive Species Awareness Week in the city, and if you follow us on social media, we'll be sharing a lot of educational information about different invasive plants and how you can get involved. This week kicks off the beginning of our invasive volunteer season, so we will be having volunteer events every couple of weeks throughout May for residents to get involved and learn how to remove invasive plants and help restore habitat in our parks. And on March 14th at the Sherwood Center, we will be having a training for those who want to get more involved or just learn how to manage invasives on their own property. All of those events can be found at FairfaxVA.gov/trees. Scroll down and the events will be there. And then I would like to pass the microphone off to Katie Johnson of Fairfax PRISM, which is a new organization helping to restore habitat and save trees from invasive plants in the city.",
      "snippet": "Perfect microphone height. Um, yeah, so this week is Invasive Species Awareness Week in the city, and if you follow us on social media, we'll be sharing a lot of educational information about different invasive plants a…"
