      "transcript_text": "Thank you. This was a great presentation. I only had a couple of comments and then 2 quick questions and maybe one that might take a little more detail. But I just wanted to say thank you, to reemphasize the strong relationships going back to the Lam Center Gala. Officer Klein was there and a few of us were there as well. And I, I felt this sense of pride being able to see him on stage and discuss more about the relationship, how he goes to Home Depot, how he talks with folks. And it really brings the humanizing side of the story that's often overlooked when it comes to homelessness. So greatly appreciate the efforts there. Happy to hear about the pilot program. So I'm very curious on how that goes. Um, when it comes to youth outreach, completely agree. Uh, as a Boys and Girls Club member when I was growing up, that was something that really impacted my life. So greatly appreciate the emphasis there. Just a couple questions. The first one related to, uh, the judicial complex. How do you see that expansion. Obviously the timeline is a little wonky, so we'll see when it happens, but how do you see the judicial complex and the role that redevelopment may play in expanding our services or providing more support to the city? I know one thing in mind was potentially a re-entry center, which talks directly on one of the topics you were talking about.",
