      "timestamp_label": "1992:14:01",
      "transcript_text": "So first, just touching on GMU, um, we have a— we actually brought on a GMU student, uh, in a master's program with, with respect to criminal justice, and she's an intern right now. and she's assigned to crime analysis. And Captain Hawkins has been working with her, and just in a short time, it's amazing what she's been able to put together with the systems that we do have. So we're very, uh, we're very excited about that, and, and we're hoping that she may be interested in continuing with us. So with respect to funding it, at the police department, we have a certain amount of funds that are available for temporary employees, contract employees, and we utilize those funds putting them to the best use, right? The things that we need to get done, the work that we need. That maybe we don't have an FTE available for that, but it's absolute— absolutely important work and critical to the organization. And so we're basically reprioritizing, and we're going to put the focus now on, on using that funding for our crime— and now crime analyst, whether it's through contract in that relationship or as a temporary employee that we bring on. And then obviously we would then work through the coming years to formalize that hopefully into an FTE, but you know, that's down the road. In the immediate, we can use this, this funding to, to address this, this, this void.",
