      "start_seconds": 7860018,
      "timestamp_label": "2183:20:18",
      "transcript_text": "I'd like to say something just in regards to what you said about source of information being the general population. People don't want to be a category. They want to be individuals. They want to be seen as human beings. A very impactful situation that I had a couple of years ago when we were going through the Homelessness Task Force, I went over and sat with 6 individuals that were guests there and heard their stories, heard what got them there. And I think it's so easy sometimes when we're dealing with, you know, these broader populations to forget that they're human beings and they're individuals and, you know, their stories are different. How they got there is different. We don't always know everything. But I think that I do agree that we need to have stakeholders and different people involved because they will tell us if we are doing it right or not. You know, I definitely got some feedback that day in regards to what struggles they have, why they sometimes don't engage. I mean, it was a very impactful situation and I think that you get valuable information by talking the stakeholders in the population, I mean, the community.",
