      "meeting_date": "2026-02-24",
      "speaker": "Councilmember Stacy Hall",
      "section": "18. Adjournment.",
      "turn_index": 136,
      "start_seconds": 11536572,
      "timestamp_label": "3204:36:12",
      "transcript_text": "Thank you. And okay, so that kind of puts things in perspective, I guess, with if we agree to do Willard Sherwood, you know, we will be signing on to this in a couple of months. If we agreed to do a new fire station, you know. So at the time of the rezoning is when it would need to be done. So there's a bit of a disincentive then, or I guess an incentive to delay, um, hearing new projects and considering new projects until we've secured potentially this opportunity that we don't want to miss out on. So what is timetable, like I think it said in the staff report that we would— the project is estimated to be completed by mid-2026. Reasonably, from a staff perspective, what are we looking for if all goes well, if this is something that it seems like it's beneficial and would help us, when would we be talking implementation?",
      "snippet": "Thank you. And okay, so that kind of puts things in perspective, I guess, with if we agree to do Willard Sherwood, you know, we will be signing on to this in a couple of months. If we agreed to do a new fire station, yo…"
