      "timestamp_label": "3249:21:54",
      "transcript_text": "[Speaker] So these are excellent questions, excellent points. If you— these are the types of projects for which you could spend those dollars on if you were collected. But those projects need to be done, you know, or expand— those types of projects need to be done. Expansion of capacity in some way, shape, or form. It doesn't necessarily have to be those exact projects, but if you collect a cash proffer for recreational facility space, those dollars should be used to expand recreational center space. Again, it doesn't need— we are not taking those projects and saying this is the $60 million project and we are dividing by the, you know, et cetera. It is what are you providing today, how do you continue to maintain that level of service. And if that is the decision of the Council to build, to do, you know, that kind of improvement to expand capacity, then those dollars can be used for that. If the decision of the Council is then to use those dollars to do an addition or to add a class, you know, add a wing or some other capacity expansion project, that's okay too. So it is, there's a methodological choice in the analysis as well, and that's, and kind of getting, we're getting a little bit ahead, but that's fine. Incremental expansion where we're saying, here's your current level of service today. You have X number of, let's just say parks, you know, X number of 5 acres per 1,000 today. If, you know, next person in, we don't have capacity for, we're going to, we're going to collect dollars and we're going to build. When we get to 1,000 people, we're going to expand, build, we're going to improve 5 acres of parkland. We're going to do a, you know, a pickleball court. We're going to do a basketball court. We're going to do a playground. You know, some kind of improvement to either an existing park where you have land to improve or a net new park. And that's also a choice too. But again, that ultimately comes out in the budget that there is a plan— there is a capital improvement plan where those dollars would be spent. [Speaker:COMMISSIONER ARKOOSH] Okay.",
