      "timestamp_label": "3670:20:01",
      "transcript_text": "Like Councilmember Ramos, I'm certainly excited to see something happening here on this site, although I, you know, don't live right across the street but am frequently in this area. And, you know, I certainly agree with all of staff's comments. And personally, you know, I also, in line with what Councilmember Ramos mentioned, I, you know, if I did live there, I'd certainly rather look out at this than what's there right now. I mean, no offense to the owner if you're out there, but frankly, it's mostly barren parking lot and then an ugly old office building. It's not really much to look at right now, whereas this, I think, has the opportunity to become really a very inviting addition to Old Town. And, you know, certainly do acknowledge that it's in a somewhat isolated location, not exactly an active commercial corridor along here. And, you know, but given that we are shooting for the maximum height that's recommended in the Small Area Plan, I think that Ideally, I'd like to see the commercial space being taken out, replaced, but if not, then perhaps at least half of it. And I mean, it's a relatively small building. I don't think that that would be a huge amount, but something to think about. But overall, I think that it's certainly heading in the right direction and can really infuse additional significant residential presence into Old Town and help support the businesses there. And then an additional point, you know, I just want to point out that the, the Flats on University right next to it is about 5 stories right there along Leighton Hall above ground, and that is directly across from Leighton Hall, whereas this is kind of more diagonally across. And so 5 stories to 6 stories, you know, I don't think I see that as a significant obstacle given that, you know, again, I think it's more separated from Layton Hall Apartments than the Flats is. So yeah, thank you. I'm very excited about this and look forward to seeing it move forward.",
