      "transcript_text": "Just a quick note, the Transportation Planning Board released what is a periodic study of traffic and transportation safety issues in the region. I think it was last week, but it's well worth a read. I may try to circulate that around, but it identifies really the biggest and most important vulnerabilities we have. For transportation safety here in the city and elsewhere and what we can do about it. And it dovetails, I think, pretty well with the conversation that we had about trying to get some help on safety— transportation safety in the Pickett Road area— because it read pretty much straight up like this was a poster child for addressing the kinds of issues they're seeing all over the place. General tenor of the report and the general tenor of the people on the Transportation Planning Board— and again, these are officials from all over the region— is we've made progress, but we're a long way from making things as safe as they need to be on the roads. There's a heck of a lot more work that needs to be done. So again, appreciate everything that we're trying to do here to push that forward. The staff here has been great about staying on top of these issues, but they're a long way from being solved. So we'll be, I'm sure, talking more about what we do with our transportation program to stay on top of that. Thanks. Councilmember Bates?",
