      "start_seconds": 11655397,
      "timestamp_label": "3237:36:37",
      "transcript_text": "Napdi. Mayor and Council, thank you for having us here this evening. Uh, joining me are Vice Chair Kirsten Lockhart and Commissioner Dr. Matt Rice. Dr. Rice is also our representative on the Parks and Recreation Advisory Board. Um, we have two other members in the commission currently. We're down were shy to, but one had other— another obligation, and Mr. Cunningham is preparing to take off early in the morning for California, so he's unable to be with us tonight as he's prepping for that. So at our meeting last night, which included our public hearing, as Mr. Napti said, Planning Commission voted unanimously to find that the projects detailed in the FY 2027 2021 capital improvement program are consistent with the city's comprehensive plan as well as other adopted city policies and priorities. As Mr. Nappi described, the vote followed our public hearing and briefings by staff. This year in particular, we met with the director of parks and recreation as well as a representative from the fire department to address a couple of questions we had on couple of projects there. So over the number of meetings that we had, we've gotten to this point and had our hearing last night. As far as what our resolution says, you have received a draft which is now the final copy. We made no changes, and we'll talk about some of these a little more detail in, in other slides. We commend to the council the CIP with some specific recommendations. There are 3 projects that we feel are particularly urgent that should be moved forward, uh, apace, and we'll talk about those. Um, and, um, those are going to be the property yard feasibility study. We continue to be concerned about, uh, the proximity of that and the location of that in the floodplain and the difficulty that's presented. Um, and it's a real threat to a lot of resources and assets in the city. Our expert in land use siting here, Dr. Rice, has kept us true to the task on looking at these, these matters in the city. And we are equally convinced as an entire commission that this is an important priority that we should be moving forward with. Did you want to add anything at this point about that?",
      "snippet": "Napdi. Mayor and Council, thank you for having us here this evening. Uh, joining me are Vice Chair Kirsten Lockhart and Commissioner Dr. Matt Rice. Dr. Rice is also our representative on the Parks and Recreation Advisor…"
