      "speaker": "Councilmember Billy Bates",
      "section": "17. Adjournment.",
      "turn_index": 257,
      "start_seconds": 14827105,
      "timestamp_label": "4118:38:25",
      "transcript_text": "I was, I was going to bring that up as well. Yeah, it's a question of purview. It's a question of purview. Mr. Mayor, you've got— you ultimately have the financial acumen and insights, a lot of which we don't have. And we have a very strong professional staff that does a very good job at estimating what a project may cost. And as it goes through redesign, we don't revisit redesigns. That's outside of our purview as well. But we do have some conversation. Conversations. It was a good example last year about the cost schedule implications of a particular project that got shifted based on some of our questions. So we do think about it. It's not our primary driver for sure.",
      "snippet": "I was, I was going to bring that up as well. Yeah, it's a question of purview. It's a question of purview. Mr. Mayor, you've got— you ultimately have the financial acumen and insights, a lot of which we don't have. And…"
