      "turn_index": 311,
      "start_seconds": 18892628,
      "timestamp_label": "5247:57:08",
      "transcript_text": "Sure. So we provide immunizations, we provide maternal child health services, that includes pregnancy pregnancy testing and referring individuals to places of care for continuation of maternity care. We provide STI and HIV testing. We provide STI treatment. We provide TB screening. So again, folks coming from other countries just needing a blood test or a skin test to see whether they're infected. And then if they are, we do the diagnosis and treatment. We provide women, infant, children, Supplemental Nutrition Program. So this is a program aimed at individuals that meet a certain income eligibility, very much similar to SNAP, except there's also a, um, a health component where we look at the child's hemoglobin level and on their— look at their growth chart. So it's the breastfeeding mom, the pregnant mom, and children up to age 5. And then we also provide, outside of clinical services, vital records, as was mentioned, which is are death certificates, birth certificates, marriage certificates, and divorce certificates. Those are the key services. Given that this is our flagship facility, our central pharmacy that provides medication for all of the rest of the other 5 departments would also be co-located there.",
