      "start_seconds": 21213859,
      "timestamp_label": "5892:44:19",
      "transcript_text": "Uh, the only other few things I'll mention is a happy belated birthday to my dad. Uh, his birthday was this past Friday. Um, thank you to everyone who helped me move into our new duplex. Greatly appreciate that. And especially during snow, that was a little rough. And then I want to echo the sentiments that Councilmember Hardy Chandler brought up with Black History Month. Um, I, I wish everyone a happy Black History Month. I hope you take the time to learn more, educate yourself. But something that I've reflected on that's kind of struck me deeply— I was watching a movie on the flight back from London. I don't know if you've seen Judas and the Black Messiah, going over the Black Panther Party in Fred Hampton. And something that just sat with me is that I'm older now than a lot of those folks who were assassinated or taken away from us early. And that's just something that rests a little heavy on my heart. So just wanted to mention that.",
