      "transcript_text": "Hey, Mayor and Council. So, uh, again, I'm Ben Rhodes. I'm a watershed professional based out of, um, Reston, obviously living here. And when we talk about, um, watersheds and stormwater in the city, the thing that I think about are our total maximum daily load action plans, our action plans for reducing pollutants of concern moving into the Potomac River and the Chesapeake Bay. Those are of particular concern for the Chesapeake Bay are phosphorus, nitrogen, and total suspended sediments. And so those are a couple of— a couple of those are what we have here when I'm looking at our existing metrics against those TMDL action plans in our reports from 2025.",
