      "transcript_text": "No, I, I greatly appreciate— this was a fantastic and very thorough presentation. Uh, I only had a few questions, but I also wanted to touch on the questions that you put on the slide deck. Uh, just starting off with that, and from my From a personal perspective, it would be prudent to probably focus on where we can get cost savings or generate funds that could help support these other projects. For example, the Solid Waste Enterprise Fund would probably be the most crucial one because that can generate a significant amount of dollars, and a portion of that or more of it can go to getting these other goals and tasks completed. Uh, and I think cost savings is something that we're looking at, not just not just with climate and energy, but overall throughout the city, where can we get more bang for our buck, especially considering some of the fiscal challenges a lot of local governments are now dealing with. When it comes to my questions, they're pretty basic. Y'all did a really good job. When it comes to the CPACE program, is that typically— are there like annual updates something you could provide? I remember that was actually one of the first decisions we made as a group, and I was actually very curious on how that's been progressing. I know it's newer program. So I'm wondering, how is that reported out per se?",
