      "start_seconds": 7915748,
      "timestamp_label": "2198:49:08",
      "transcript_text": "Okay, I definitely support that. I— that was the $55,000. I think that's a huge, huge asset for our community. Um, I will say too, with Solarize Virginia, uh, we were fortunate to take advantage of the solar energy credit before the end of the year, but with the elimination of the federal tax credit and no state tax credit, I do think the conversion from, uh, homeowners and residents might slow down pretty significantly. A resident did message me during this meeting— they're watching from home— and they suggested that maybe the Renaissance program could start to include solar as a priority for upgrades to homes. I don't— I know when we did the Renaissance program, I don't— that wasn't on our radar at all back then, but I thought it was an interesting thought. And then I think my other question, and I don't I don't expect you to get back to me right now, but you had mentioned that some of the programs had been delayed due to previous city manager, and I was just curious if you could let us know what programs were delayed, uh, how that has hindered you and what you're doing, and how we can try to get back on track with that as soon as possible.",
