      "start_seconds": 1049008,
      "timestamp_label": "291:23:28",
      "transcript_text": "Good evening. Douglas Stewart, 10822 Maple Street. I too live in Westmore. I've— we've lived there for 21 years now. I am unqualifiedly in support of this project. I think it's going to be a great project. It's only going to further the connections between our neighborhood and Camp Washington, they're getting better and better. And Camp Washington is getting better and better. It's really exciting to see as somebody who's looked for more walkable connections to the nearby area. It's really impressive to see how that Small Area Plan is materializing. Just stepping back, when the Small Area Plan for Camp Washington was being developed, the Westmoor Civic Association was very actively involved in that. And I want to give a shout out to the former president of Westmoor Civic Association, Beth Iannetta, because she was very involved. She was working with Federal Realty, the developer of that shopping center where Aldi and CVS is, right adjacent to the Fern Street. She was working with city staff. She was working with city council members and planning commissioners, and there was a lot of Honestly, there was a lot of division and different opinions about how that Fern Street connection should happen and what it should look like. There were some discussion and people in favor of a motorized connection. A lot of neighbors were very concerned about that. And I just want to just commend the city staff and everybody really for making this work and working with the community to develop such a great connection that's going for people who are just It is just a 2-minute walk to Hiraz from Park Street. I mean, it's a very easy thing to do. And this is one of those connections that's just making it easier. It's going to be— and when you're getting Fern Street extended to where the Shake Shack is, when you get that light there, that's going to be a game changer. And these things are happening. And I've seen them happen as somebody who's lived there for a long time. This is actually happening. It's happening fairly quickly. I've always wanted our son, who's now 23, 3 to be able to walk to areas. And he's gotten to the point where he has his driver's license. He doesn't really care about walking. But I still— we're seeing it happen for our kids. And I'm really excited about it. The only comment I'd make about the actual project is when you're maintaining it, I hope you'll work with the Environmental Sustainability Committee. We have a lot of expertise in the city about— especially about the the native plants and the landscaping. And this is a great opportunity to work with neighbors and other people, other residents, on maintaining that and even further improving it as we go along. So great project. I'm very excited. Thank you.",
