      "timestamp_label": "340:54:19",
      "transcript_text": "Is there anybody else in the room that would like to talk on the Fern Street? Yep. You may come forward, ma'am. And just please state your name and address with your comment. Hi, good evening. My name is Beth Ayaneda. I'm a resident of Westmoor at 10916 Berry Street. I'll have to correct Doug on my title. Still President, also VP, partial Treasurer, Web Designer, Public Outreach, Parks Committee, Transportation. You name it, we've got it, all in one house. So I just wanted to say Westmoor is It's an unbelievable community. We mark our 75th year this year of when it was first founded in 1951, if you can imagine, and what they were talking about was extending gas to homes. Our mailboxes were on a public dirt street at the end of the road at Chestnut, and so we've come a long way. And so it's great to see these improvements happening, and so I am supportive of it. I will say, and I will shame myself, In my support of it, I was a transportation planner for most of my county career, and I never rode the Fairfax Connector bus. And I've— they recently changed the route to serve near our community to go to the Government Center. So I've rode the bus more in my 25 years in the county rep just because of walking this path from my house down Fern Street, across the grass area that the trail is going into the bus stop. It's across the street near Chipotle. I will say keep pushing for a pedestrian connection across that roadway. I recently had my father visit and he froggered his way across Route 29 and I was very concerned for him. So anyway, I just wanted to say I think staff has done a really great job reaching out. I know on Facebook we had some comments, they were overwhelmed with the outreach, so keep it up. I greatly support it. Keep out the outreach and keep it going. And so I just want to say I think everyone's done a really great job in trying to get these improvements that our community has waited for for a very, very long time. We have a lot of missing pieces, but this I think will help. We also have the new businesses coming in. When we're working with Federal Realty, they've also changed their— the front of the buildings and done some improvements. We have a mural out there now that you'll walk by when you use this walkway. So there's really been a lot of investment coming in like inches and, you know, leaps and bounds, but I think this is yet another piece that will get you there. For me personally, the only comment I will say I wish it was 8 feet, not 10. I know it's a nitpicky thing, but I would just want it to be a more context-sensitive solution to the size of the shape that it is. It's very small. It is defined as right-of-way. It is not a park. It's a street. And so what lies in streets is utilities that you don't see under the ground. And so I think a lot of the costs are what they're reflected in that because there's drainage that you don't see. There's a lot of utilities that you don't see that run through there because it's designated as a road. Even though it's not a road. But anyway, thank you all. I greatly appreciate it for the time, and I just want to say we support the project for myself and hopefully to look for more in the future. Thank you very much. Is there anybody else in the room? Yeah, ma'am, you may come forward, and sir, you can go after her. Hi, my name is Romy and Joe. We are the residents of 11,000 Park Road, which is directly affected from this path. Maybe we are the only residential area facing this path. So we are happy to have this lovely path, but I have a couple of questions. And comments. First of all, we have a fence along this path, but the fence height is limited. Because many people will pass by the path, is it possible if we can get the higher fence, like 7 feet? That's our one question. And then my second question is Are you going to have a security camera somewhere? Because we are next to this path. That's my question. And then also the third question is, you are going to have a construction end of this year. And then how that construction is going to be— will be, because we'll have a tenant. We have to notify them. What's the impact of their life there? So those are the three comments. I'm happy to have this wonderful path, but also I have decent concerns because we are directly affected from this path.",
