      "transcript_text": "Good evening again, Mayor and Council. This one is a brief housekeeping item. The staff report is self-explanatory. The city code was last recodified in 2000. As you're aware, from time to time ordinances come before the, um, before the city council amending provisions of the city code. The recodification, when we did that, had a provision that said those automatically became part of the city code. Unicode, the company that puts up most most municipal codes in Virginia and in other states as well will periodically publish supplements. And as noted, there's no requirement, requirement that we incorporate those by action, but I believe it's best practice from time to time to do this. So the item before you this evening would formally incorporate supplement numbers 16 through 26 inclusive into the Code of the City of Fairfax. Happy to answer any questions.",
