      "transcript_text": "I think we talked about this once before, and the issue of the deputy came up. It— so it sounds like our conclusion— I think the issue at the time was, should that be done? And the event that somebody steps in as an alternate. And I— and it sounds like we've concluded that's either unnecessary or that could be addressed on an as-needed basis. Is that fair? That's correct. I think the thinking on this would be, uh, there are obviously many circumstances under which a sort of a temporary deputy acting as a department head, you know, illness, extended absence, um, we don't believe certainly that that's an occasion for requiring a disclosure form. if the person is acting in a significant period of time, we can always alter and require disclosure at that point.",
