      "timestamp_label": "737:31:48",
      "transcript_text": "Thank you, Mayor, Council. As discussed at the November 4th City Council Work Session and introduced at the December 9th City Council Regular Meeting, the City of Fairfax has previously been awarded $20.6 million in I-66 Outside the Beltway Project Concessionaire Funding for the George Schneider Trail project. The city recently received construction bids that exceeded the $16 million remaining in the project budget. The estimate to complete the project with additional costs such as contingency, construction management, and VDOT oversight will exceed the remaining budget by $4.6 million. There is additional concessionaire funding available in the balance entry account at VDOT to accommodate the city's funding need. Accordingly, the City requested this funding via the Northern Virginia Transportation Authority, NVTA, which is the entity that makes recommendations for this funding to the Commonwealth Transportation Board, also known as CTB.",
