      "start_seconds": 5667450,
      "timestamp_label": "1574:17:30",
      "transcript_text": "My name is Jeff Mann. I am at 9744 Cardinal Road in the great city of Fairfax. I have heard many eloquent people tonight on both sides of the issue. But I, I encourage you to vote no. Um, this— we need safety and we need walkways and we need, uh, things like that in this city, but we do not need the George Schneider Trail as proposed because it's bloated. The, uh, environmental study that was done on it is flawed. There are protected species and wetlands out there that are going to be decimated. It's It's the last, one of the last stands in the city of hardwood forest, and it's beautiful like the gentleman spoke about before. I've walked around it with my family, and it's wonderful. And the animals we haven't even talked about, like the blue heron that's in there, the one that I've seen. There might be more. It's always there. The ducks, the fox, the raccoons, all of that is going to be messed up. Mr. Ito, word on the street is, has decided not to plant some of the trees in the stream restoration because it's going to mess up what's proposed for the George Schneider Trail. So that's even less trees that are going to go up because the Schneider Trail is going to decimate more trees. Um, it's a tough decision, and, and you guys work hard, I know that, but you've got to think of your fiduciary responsibility to the citizens and the future of Fairfax City and my son and the people who come in and move in here years and years and years from now. Don't get rid of those woods. Don't mess up those woods. It's the only thing we've got that really lets us know that we're a tree city. I mean, we speak out of both sides of our mouths, and it's kind of crazy. It's time to stop the madness.",
      "snippet": "My name is Jeff Mann. I am at 9744 Cardinal Road in the great city of Fairfax. I have heard many eloquent people tonight on both sides of the issue. But I, I encourage you to vote no. Um, this— we need safety and we nee…"
