      "timestamp_label": "4033:42:49",
      "transcript_text": "Councilmember Hardy Chandler. Um, in addition to Law Enforcement Appreciation Day, we had the opportunity to attend the fire department's promotion and, uh, awards day, which was Fantastic. Always, it's a great opportunity to hear the heroic stories of those who are serving our cities through the fire department and the volunteer fire department, as well as the EMTs. And, um, really appreciate that. I want to— I feel a little bit compelled to issue both an apology and an invitation. An apology because I do believe that there are consequences to each council's legacy, and I believe that there will be consequences that future councils will certainly have to navigate. But I also want to issue an invitation because I do think that while it's very wonderful for people to acknowledge how difficult it is to to be up here. I want to invite people who don't see themselves as being a part of City Council to consider running. Um, this is that time when people are collecting signatures and getting on the ballot. I do believe that there is room for a very holistic voice on this council. So I definitely— first of all, if you haven't thought about it, I really encourage you follow up with your engagement by serving your city in this way and, and consider getting on the ballot and serving on City Council.",
