      "transcript_text": "Uh, just echoing thanks to everyone who showed up today. Thank you, Dan. Welcome to the show. Uh, you probably won't see the room packed like that for a little while anyway, so, uh, let's Sink or swim. Otherwise, letting folks know this upcoming Monday is MLK Jr. Day. Volunteer Fairfax will be doing their Day of Service. Please go out, volunteer in your community, be a part. They're going to be doing events everywhere. I think this year they've done it at Sherwood before. I know they did it at NVCC. So I'm not sure where it's at this time, but you can just Google Volunteer Fairfax and find it. You know what, I'll touch on that another time. I'm going to London tomorrow, so I will catch y'all in a week. So if I'm slow to respond, it's because I'm not allowed to take my city equipment with me. So my bad. And spoilers, I'm buying a house. So I will be, you know, for those who complain about me renting in the city, I'll be a homeowner now. I pay taxes either way, but there you go. All right. Have a good one.",
