      "transcript_text": "Thank You Stacey. Good evening mayor members of City Council and as I understand it new city manager Congratulations again. My name is James Mikkel and I'm a consultant manager with Barry Dunn I've been with that firm for Four years and previous to then I spent over 20 years as a recreation professional with the city of Norfolk as an administrator I spent a year and a half as Assistant to the city manager and then I spent 15 years with Boys and Girls Club as the executive director my entire career has been Rooted in youth development and community servitude. So Transitioning consulting has been absolutely amazing For me. Thank you for having me So Today I'd like to tell you a little bit about the status of the parks and recreation master plan Give you a little background on the project's scheduling approach Some of our project highlights are mainly in community engagement And then I like to engage you a little bit with a few questions and an exercise to gather some information from you It's a part of our information gathering process So I told you a little about me just a little bit about Barry Dunn because they required me to do this Barry Dunn was founded in 1974 as an accounting firm and then 30 years later They ventured into consulting and they ventured into consulting in many different realms to include Medicare local government Feasibility studies strategic master planning five years ago. They learned that parks and recreation master planning could be a vital Addition to the department. So we began our practice five years ago Unique about our practices that we are a group of 30 who have all been administrators and parks and recreation So we're rooted in the field We speak the language and we understand what individuals like Stacy and what Katie go to on a day-to-day But we aren't just parks and recreation professionals We're also trained project managers and we've done this on over 500 projects in just five years myself I think I've worked on 45",
