      "start_seconds": 228,
      "timestamp_label": "03:48",
      "transcript_text": "So just a little background into the core components of a scalable parks and recreation master plan and this these are Four components that's typically a part of any strategic master plan not just for parks and recreation But it could be a comprehensive plan for a city state or any department or for any park Step one or component one is information gathering and that's the needs assessment That's inventory level of service To include the community profile The community profile is typically your demographics and trends because when you're completing this type of work It's important to understand who you're serving and what they desire Right if we're going to build a plan for ten years It'd be hard to build a plan for what your demographics and what your community look like now You have to be able to estimate what it looked like in ten years. So you're building a plan. That's not only comprehensive, but one That you would be able to use and be a living breathing document phase two is Findings and visioning and this is after we've gathered all of our information. We've spoken with the community We've spoken with internal staff. We've reviewed your parks. We've looked at your operations organizational assessment Looked at captain improvement for the last few years and some of the things we may recommend for the future Then we come back to the department and we partner with them to build what the recommendations may look like As I mentioned with a team of 30 who have worked in parks and recreation for many years We probably could get together and figure out some Pretty good recommendations some that would be comprehensive But it's important to ensure that you utilize and the staff that would be implementing it that have skin in the game So building the recommendations based on key findings that we've learned through information gathering that we've learned through analysis Really makes our plans one that can be implemented. It's a living breathing document that you can use for the course of the plan From there I go and lock myself in the room and I write a draft It may take me a few weeks. It may take me a few hours I don't know but we write a draft and then we present that to council and then a final plan that we design and we teach You how to implement it over the course of ten years",
